{"title_page": "Cryphia moeonis", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = \n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Cryphia moeonis\n| authority = ([[Julius Lederer (entomologist)|Lederer]], 1865)\n| synonyms =\n*''Cryphia maeonis''\n*''Bryophila moeonis'' <small>Lederer, 1865</small>\n*''Bryophila praecana'' <small>Christoph, 1893</small>\n*''Bryophila maeonis f. centralis'' <small>Draudt, 1931</small>\n*''Bryophila centralis occidentalis'' <small>Osthelder, 1933</small>\n}} \n'''''Cryphia moeonis''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Noctuidae]]. It is found in the [[Near East]] and [[Middle East]], mainly in [[steppe]]s and semi-deserts. In the [[Levant]] it is found in [[Jordan]] and [[Israel]].\n\nAdults are on wing from June to August. There is one generation per year.\n\nThe larvae probably feed on [[lichen]].\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/455/45513509.pdf The Acronictinae, Bryophilinae, Hypenodinae and Hypeninae of Israel]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5190569}}\n\n[[Category:Cryphia]]\n[[Category:Moths of the Middle East]]\n[[Category:Moths described in 1865]]\n\n\n{{Bryophilinae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = \n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Cryphia moeonis\n| authority = ([[Julius Lederer (entomologist)|Lederer]], 1865)\n| synonyms =\n*''Cryphia maeonis''\n*''Bryophila moeonis'' <small>Lederer, 1865</small>\n*''Bryophila praecana'' <small>Christoph, 1893</small>\n*''Bryophila maeonis f. centralis'' <small>Draudt, 1931</small>\n*''Bryophila centralis occidentalis'' <small>Osthelder, 1933</small>\n}} \n'''''Cryphia moeonis''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Noctuidae]]. It is found in the [[Near East]] and [[Middle East]], mainly in [[steppe]]s and semi-deserts. In the [[Levant]] it is found in [[Jordan]] and [[Israel]].\n\nAdults are on wing from June to August. There is one generation per year.\n\nThe larvae probably feed on [[lichen]].\n\n==External links==\n*[http://redalyc.uaemex.mx/redalyc/html/455/45513509/45513509.html The Acronictinae, Bryophilinae, Hypenodinae and Hypeninae of Israel]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5190569}}\n\n[[Category:Cryphia]]\n[[Category:Moths of the Middle East]]\n[[Category:Moths described in 1865]]\n\n\n{{Bryophilinae-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Logan", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:bad link repair", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryphia_moeonis"}
{"title_page": "Cryphia labecula", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = \n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Cryphia labecula\n| authority = ([[Julius Lederer (entomologist)|Lederer]], 1855)\n| synonyms =\n}}\n\n'''''Cryphia labecula''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Noctuidae]]. It is found in the [[Lebanon]] mountain range the adjacent southern part of [[Turkey]] and [[Mount Hermon]] in the [[Golan Heights]].\n\nAdults are on wing from May to June. There is probably one generation per year.\n\nThe larvae probably feed on [[lichen]].\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/455/45513509.pdf The Acronictinae, Bryophilinae, Hypenodinae and Hypeninae of Israel]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5190567}}\n\n[[Category:Cryphia]]\n[[Category:Moths of the Middle East]]\n[[Category:Moths described in 1855]]\n\n\n{{Bryophilinae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = \n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Cryphia labecula\n| authority = ([[Julius Lederer (entomologist)|Lederer]], 1855)\n| synonyms =\n}}\n\n'''''Cryphia labecula''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Noctuidae]]. It is found in the [[Lebanon]] mountain range the adjacent southern part of [[Turkey]] and [[Mount Hermon]] in the [[Golan Heights]].\n\nAdults are on wing from May to June. There is probably one generation per year.\n\nThe larvae probably feed on [[lichen]].\n\n==External links==\n*[http://redalyc.uaemex.mx/redalyc/html/455/45513509/45513509.html The Acronictinae, Bryophilinae, Hypenodinae and Hypeninae of Israel]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5190567}}\n\n[[Category:Cryphia]]\n[[Category:Moths of the Middle East]]\n[[Category:Moths described in 1855]]\n\n\n{{Bryophilinae-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Logan", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:bad link repair", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryphia_labecula"}
{"title_page": "Cryphia rectilinea", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = \n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Cryphia rectilinea\n| authority = (Warren, 1909)\n| synonyms =\n*''Metachrostis rectilinea'' <small>Warren, 1909</small>\n*''Cryphia rectilinea insulicola'' <small>Reisser, 1962</small>\n}} \n'''''Cryphia rectilinea''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Noctuidae]]. It is found in the [[Balkan]]s, [[Italy]], [[Turkey]], [[Lebanon]] and [[Israel]].\n\n== Life cycle ==\nAdults are on wing from May to September. There is one generation per year.\n\nThe larvae probably feed on [[lichen]].\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/455/45513509.pdf The Acronictinae, Bryophilinae, Hypenodinae and Hypeninae of Israel]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5190578}}\n\n[[Category:Cryphia]]\n[[Category:Moths of the Middle East]]\n[[Category:Moths described in 1909]]\n\n\n{{Bryophilinae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = \n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Cryphia rectilinea\n| authority = (Warren, 1909)\n| synonyms =\n*''Metachrostis rectilinea'' <small>Warren, 1909</small>\n*''Cryphia rectilinea insulicola'' <small>Reisser, 1962</small>\n}} \n'''''Cryphia rectilinea''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Noctuidae]]. It is found in the [[Balkan]]s, [[Italy]], [[Turkey]], [[Lebanon]] and [[Israel]].\n\n== Life cycle ==\nAdults are on wing from May to September. There is one generation per year.\n\nThe larvae probably feed on [[lichen]].\n\n==External links==\n*[http://redalyc.uaemex.mx/redalyc/html/455/45513509/45513509.html The Acronictinae, Bryophilinae, Hypenodinae and Hypeninae of Israel]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5190578}}\n\n[[Category:Cryphia]]\n[[Category:Moths of the Middle East]]\n[[Category:Moths described in 1909]]\n\n\n{{Bryophilinae-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Logan", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:bad link repair", "