{"title_page": "Cryphia amseli", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = \n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Cryphia amseli\n| authority = Boursin, 1952\n| synonyms =\n}} \n'''''Cryphia amseli''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Noctuidae]]. It is probably endemic to the arid part of the [[Jordan Rift Valley]]. It is known only from the type locality: [[Israel]], [[Jericho]], April 1952. It has not been observed since.\n\nThere is probably one generation per year.\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/455/45513509.pdf The Acronictinae, Bryophilinae, Hypenodinae and Hypeninae of Israel]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5190566}}\n\n[[Category:Cryphia]]\n[[Category:Moths of the Middle East]]\n[[Category:Moths described in 1952]]\n\n\n{{Bryophilinae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = \n| image = \n| image_caption = \n| taxon = Cryphia amseli\n| authority = Boursin, 1952\n| synonyms =\n}} \n'''''Cryphia amseli''''' is a [[moth]] of the family [[Noctuidae]]. It is probably endemic to the arid part of the [[Jordan Rift Valley]]. It is known only from the type locality: [[Israel]], [[Jericho]], April 1952. It has not been observed since.\n\nThere is probably one generation per year.\n\n==External links==\n*[http://redalyc.uaemex.mx/redalyc/html/455/45513509/45513509.html The Acronictinae, Bryophilinae, Hypenodinae and Hypeninae of Israel]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5190566}}\n\n[[Category:Cryphia]]\n[[Category:Moths of the Middle East]]\n[[Category:Moths described in 1952]]\n\n\n{{Bryophilinae-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Logan", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:bad link repair", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryphia_amseli"}
